      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CASE FORTY EIGHT (1) is a quality gelding who has managed three wins and three minor placings from six starts this time in work. Went back last start then worked home in good style to salute by 1.1 metres at Ararat over 1790m, his second win in a row. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. This doesn't look as hard so he is in the right race to win again. ROBLEN RANGER (2) scored last time out by a head in a far better performance at Hamilton over 2160m. Has the ability to take care of this field. ROCKABILLY RINGO (10) ended last prep with a win at Globe Derby Park over 2230m four-and-a-half months ago. Capable of a forward showing while fresh. KEAYANG PAYTON (4) won the only time she raced here and is proven fresh.",
